The paper describes the use of deep convolutional neural networks for Raman spectrum recognition, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of machine learning algorithms such as support vector machines and principal component analysis also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method compared to other methods, which may suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of computational engineering (cs.CE).
